# Conventional Commit Message Template
#
# See CONTRIBUTING.md for details: https://github.com/your-username/transity/blob/develop/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md#commit-message-guidelines
#
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#         -- blank line --
#         <body>
#         -- blank line --
#         <footer>
#
# Example:
# feat(simulation): add passenger routing algorithm
#
# Implement A* pathfinding for passenger route calculation.
# - Add priority queue implementation
# - Add path reconstruction
# - Add distance heuristic function
#
# Closes #123

# --- Commit Header ---
# Type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, chore, ci
# Scope: Optional - Component affected (e.g., core, simulation, gui, build, docs)
# Subject: Imperative, present tense, lowercase, no period, max 72 chars.

# --- Commit Body (Optional) ---
# - Imperative, present tense.
# - Explain *why* vs. *what*. Motivation, contrast with previous behavior.
# - Wrap at 72 characters.


# --- Commit Footer (Optional) ---
# - Reference related issues/PRs (e.g., Closes #123, Fixes #456, Ref #789).
# - Breaking changes: Start with `BREAKING CHANGE:` followed by description.


# --- END TEMPLATE ---